originalText.text: I have been seeing Dr. Chabla for several years and there was a point and time where I would have given him a good review.  As a Dr. he is fine and thorough, but the clinic is not run well.  Expect to wait for 3+ hours.  Just because you have an appointment it doesn't mean anything they take people on a first come first serve basis and don't explain the policy beforehand. I had an appointment for today and the attendant couldn't locate me on the computer, even though I had been receiving email and phone reminders of the appointment.  Very unorganized staff and unprofessional scheduling policy.

I really love my doctor. I been his patient for over 9 years.  People have the misconception about medical office /appointments.
This is not a in and out service center, its a clinic. Meaning that all proper steps needs to be follow. If you are looking for better health, good treatment and proper diagnoses please I advice you to be patient and have patience.  We should all know by now that appointment does not mean that you will be call at the exact time you have scheduled it. You have to get triage,  and wait for your turn.  Doctors have to see several patient's and they as well as you deserve the time to mannerly be seen.
